'''''[[Sacred Games (TV series)|ᱥᱟᱠᱨᱮᱰ ᱜᱮᱢᱥ]]''''' ᱥᱤᱨᱤᱡ ᱨᱮᱭᱟᱜ ᱥᱟᱩᱸᱰ ᱴᱨᱟᱠ ᱫᱚ ᱒᱔ ᱴᱨᱟᱠ ᱟᱱᱤᱡ ᱾ ᱚᱱᱟ ᱵᱷᱤᱛᱤᱨ ᱨᱮ ᱗ ᱜᱚᱴᱟᱝ ᱥᱮᱨᱮᱧ ᱟᱨ ᱥᱠᱳᱨᱥ ᱠᱚ ᱢᱮᱱᱟᱜ ᱟᱱᱤᱡ ᱾ <ref>{{cite AV media|title=Sacred Games Songs: Audio Jukebox|work=Netflix}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tunefind.com/show/sacred-games/season-1|title=Sacred Games soundtrack|publisher=Tune find|accessdate=3 August 2018}}</ref> ᱥᱮᱨᱮᱧ "Kaam 25" ᱫᱚ [[Divine (rapper)|ᱰᱤᱵᱷᱟᱭᱤᱱ]] ᱠᱚ ᱡᱚᱲᱟᱣ ᱟᱠᱟᱫᱟ ᱟᱨ ᱱᱚᱣᱟ ᱨᱮ ᱥᱮᱨᱮᱧ ᱯᱨᱚᱰᱭᱩᱥᱚᱨ ᱫᱚ [[Phenom_(rock_group)|ᱯᱷᱮᱱᱚᱢ]] ᱢᱮᱱᱟᱭᱟ ᱾ ᱱᱚᱣᱟ ᱥᱮᱨᱮᱧ ᱫᱚ ᱒᱑ ᱡᱩᱱ ᱒᱐᱑᱘ ᱨᱮ ᱨᱤᱞᱤᱡ ᱠᱟᱱᱟ ᱾ <ref name=divine>{{cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/sacred-games-divine-talks-about-the-inspiration-behind-kaam-25-uncovering-the-dark-side-of-mumbai-4576951.html|title=Sacred Games: DIVINE talks about the inspiration behind 'Kaam 25', uncovering the dark side of Mumbai|last=Jain|first=Sidhantha|work=Firstpost|date=5 July 2018|accessdate=5 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180705180452/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/sacred-games-divine-talks-about-the-inspiration-behind-kaam-25-uncovering-the-dark-side-of-mumbai-4576951.html|archive-date=5 July 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> ᱱᱚᱣᱟ ᱫᱚ ᱥᱤᱨᱤᱡ ᱨᱮ ᱵᱟᱠᱚ ᱥᱮᱞᱮᱫ ᱞᱮᱟ ᱾ ᱥᱤᱫᱷᱟᱱᱛᱚ ᱡᱮᱱ ᱟᱜ ᱢᱮᱱ ᱞᱮᱠᱟᱛᱮ ᱱᱚᱣᱟ ᱠᱚ ᱫᱚ ''Firstpost'', the song is a "hard-hitting, hypnotic Mumbai anthem inspired by the streets."<ref name=divine/> One of Divine's earlier song ᱰᱤᱵᱷᱟᱭᱤ ᱟᱜ ᱯᱩᱭᱞᱩ ᱥᱮᱨᱮᱧ "Jungli Sher" ᱦᱚᱸ ᱱᱚᱣᱟ ᱟᱤᱨᱤᱡ ᱨᱮ ᱠᱚ‌ ᱥᱮᱞᱮᱫ ᱟᱠᱟᱫᱟ ᱾ <ref name=divine/> ᱵᱮᱠᱜᱨᱟᱩᱸᱰ ᱥᱠᱳᱨ ᱟᱨ ᱯᱷᱮᱰᱟᱛ ᱛᱷᱤᱢ ᱫᱚ [[ᱟᱞᱳᱠᱟᱱᱚᱱᱫᱚ ᱫᱟᱥ ᱜᱳᱯᱛᱟ]] ᱜᱮ ᱵᱮᱱᱟᱣ ᱞᱮᱟᱭ ᱾ <ref name=aloka>{{cite web|url=https://scroll.in/reel/885874/dark-criminal-funny-with-truth-underneath-alokananda-dasgupta-on-the-music-of-sacred-games|title='Dark, criminal, funny, with truth underneath': Alokananda Dasgupta on the music of 'Sacred Games'|last=Ghosh|first=Devarsi|publisher=Scroll.in|date=15 July 2018|accessdate=2 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180802223457/https://scroll.in/reel/885874/dark-criminal-funny-with-truth-underneath-alokananda-dasgupta-on-the-music-of-sacred-games|archive-date=2 August 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> ᱟᱞᱳᱠᱟᱱᱚᱱᱫᱚ ᱫᱚ ᱱᱚᱣᱟ ᱨᱮᱱᱟᱝ "Saiyaan", "Tabahi", "Dhuaan Dhuaan" and "Kukoo's Couplet" ᱥᱮᱨᱮᱧ ᱠᱚ ᱦᱚᱸ ᱵᱮᱱᱟᱮ ᱟᱠᱟᱫᱟ ᱾ <ref name=aloka/> ᱫᱟᱥ ᱜᱳᱯᱛᱟ ᱟᱨ ᱢᱚᱛᱣᱟᱱᱤ ᱛᱤᱠᱤᱱᱟᱜ ᱢᱮᱱ ᱞᱮᱠᱟᱛᱮ ᱫᱚ ᱵᱮᱠᱜᱨᱟᱩᱸᱰ ᱛᱷᱤᱢ ᱠᱚ ᱫᱚ ᱫᱷᱚᱨᱚᱢ ᱵᱤᱫᱟ.ᱞ‌ᱛᱮ ᱵᱮᱱᱟᱣ ᱢᱟ ᱾ ᱢᱮᱱᱠᱷᱟᱱ ᱚᱠᱟ ᱫᱷᱚᱨᱚᱢ ᱦᱚᱸ ᱟᱞᱚᱠᱚ ᱥᱮᱞᱮᱫ ᱢᱟ ᱾ <ref name=aloka/> [[ᱨᱚᱪᱤᱛᱟ ᱟᱨᱳᱨᱟ]] ᱱᱚᱣᱟ ᱨᱮᱱᱟᱝ "Disco Capital" and "Labon Se Chhukar." ᱥᱮᱨᱮᱧ ᱛᱮᱭᱟᱨ ᱟᱠᱟᱫᱟ ᱾ She was briefed by Kashyap to listen to the songs of ᱠᱚᱥᱭᱚᱯ ᱟᱜ ᱢᱮᱱᱛᱮ ᱱᱩᱭ ᱫᱚ [[ᱵᱟᱯᱤ ᱞᱤᱦᱤᱨᱤ]] ᱟᱜ ᱟᱮᱨᱮᱧ ᱠᱚ ᱟᱱᱡᱟᱢ ᱵᱟᱲᱟ ᱭᱮᱫ ᱛᱟᱦᱮᱸᱫ ᱛᱚᱵᱮ ᱮᱱᱟᱝ ᱥᱮ ᱥᱮᱨᱮᱧ ᱵᱮᱱᱟᱣ ᱨᱮᱭᱟᱜ ᱡᱤᱣᱤ ᱫᱚ ᱥᱟᱨᱮᱲᱚᱜ-ᱟ ᱾ "<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/sacred-games-composer-rachita-arora-gender-doesnt-matter-in-the-music-field/19649198|title=Sacred Games' Composer Rachita Arora: Gender Doesn't Matter In The Music Field|last=Maskeri|first=Anju|work=Mid Day|date=29 July 2018|accessdate=3 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180803104506/https://www.mid-day.com/articles/sacred-games-composer-rachita-arora-gender-doesnt-matter-in-the-music-field/19649198|archive-date=3 August 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> ᱱᱚᱣᱟ ᱠᱚ ᱥᱮᱨᱮᱧ ᱫᱚ ᱨᱟᱡᱮᱥᱣᱚᱨᱤ ᱫᱟᱥ ᱜᱳᱯᱛᱟ,ᱯᱨᱚᱠᱷᱚᱨ ᱢᱤᱥᱨᱚ ᱵᱚᱨᱩᱬᱮᱱᱫᱨᱚ,ᱵᱤᱥᱟᱞ ᱥᱟᱣᱚᱸᱛ ᱟᱨ ᱨᱟᱡᱮᱥᱣᱚᱨᱤ ᱫᱮᱥ ᱯᱟᱱᱰᱮ ᱮᱢᱟᱱ ᱠᱚ ᱚᱞ ᱟᱠᱟᱫᱟ ᱾
